<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/7172> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #7172" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/5> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "A senator adlected by Caesar? See Wiseman (CQ 14, 1964, 132-133; NM 281, no. 539), who discusses three possible Licini: one, a barber mentioned in Horace (AP 300-301); second, a senator, confused with him, who was adlected by Caesar (Comm. Cruq. on Hor. loc. cit.; Schol. on Persius 2.56; and Anth. Pal. [ed. Riese] 268, no. 414, from Varro of Atax); and third, the notorious freedman of Augustus (cf. Dio 54.21.2- 8). Wiseman suggests that the senator was the husband of Teidia Sex. f., identified as the L. Se]ius L. f. Pom. Licinus (Latomus 22, 1963, 87-90), one of an earlier generation in the family of Seianus from Volsinii.[124x]\n" .
